icilindrica|250 Bicilindrica]] 1959\u20131961\n*  [[MV Agusta 350 racers#MV Agusta 350 4C 1954-1964|350 four]] 1954\u20131964\n*  [[MV Agusta 350 racers#MV Agusta 350 2C 1957|350 twin]] 1957\n*  [[MV Agusta 350 racers#MV Agusta 350 6C 1957|350 six]] 1957\n*  [[MV Agusta 350 racers#MV Agusta 350 3C 1965-1973|350 three]] 1965\u20131973\n*  [[MV Agusta 350 racers#MV Agusta 350 6C 1968|350 six]] 1968\n*  [[MV Agusta 350 racers#MV Agusta 350 4C 1972-1976|350 four]] 1972\u20131976\n*  [[MV Agusta 500 racers#MV Agusta 500 4C 1950-1966|500 four]] 1950-1966\n*  [[MV Agusta 500 Three|500 three]] 1966\u20131973\n*  [[MV Agusta 500 Four|500 four]] 1973\u20131976\n*  [[MV Agusta 500 Six|500 six]]  1957\u20131958\n\n==Modern product history (from 1998)==\n\n===MV Agusta F4 ===\n{{main|MV Agusta F4 series}}\n[[File:MVAgusta F4 750.JPG|thumb|right|MV Agusta F4 750 S]]\n[[File:MV Agusta F4 1000 R 312.jpg|thumb|right|MV Agusta F4 1000 R 312]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- \n! colspan=2 | 1st Generation \n! 2nd Generation\n|-\n! 750 cc \n! 1,000 / 1,078 cc\n! 1,000 cc\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Production models \n|-\n| {{bulleted list|[[MV Agusta F4 series#F4 750 S|F4 750 S]] (2000)|[[MV Agusta F4 series#F4 750 S|F4 750 S 1+1]] (2000)|[[MV Agusta F4 series#F4 750 S Evo 02|F4 750 S Evo 02]] (2002)|[[MV Agusta F4 series#F4 750 S Evo 02|F4 750 S Evo 02 1+1]] (2002)|[[MV Agusta F4 series#F4 750 S Evo 03|F4 750 S Evo 03]] (2003)|[[MV Agusta F4 series#F4 750 S Evo 03|F4 750 S Evo 03 1+1]] (2003)}} \n| {{bulleted list|[[MV Agusta F4 series#F4 1000 S|F4 1000 S]] (2005)|[[MV Agusta F4 series#F4 1000 S|F4 1000 S 1+1]] (2005)|[[MV Agusta F4 series#F4 1000 R|F4 1000 R]] (2007)|[[MV Agusta F4 series#F4 1000 R|F4 1000 R 1+1]] (2007)|[[MV Agusta F4 series#F4 R 312|F4 R 312]] (2008)|[[MV Agusta F4 series#F4 RR 312|F4 RR 312]] (2009)}}\n| {{bulleted list|[[MV Agusta F4 series#F4|F4]] (2010)|[[MV Agusta F4 series#F4 RR|F4 RR]] (2011)|[[MV Agusta F4 series#F4 R|F4 R]] (2012)}}\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Limited edition 